dataIdInfo.idPurp: This is a coverage developed by the Neponset River Watershed Association summrizing the results of its inventory of dams in the Watershed. This layer reflects dams which have been evaluated by NepRWA volunteers and staff. This file was very carefully reconciled with dam datalayers obtained from DFG DER in 2003, 2005 and 2013. Dams inspected by NepRWA are included here. Sites inspected and found not to contain dams are included in the "NepRWA_Not_A_Dam" coverage. Dams identified by DER or by NepRWA's own investigations, but which have not yet been inspected are included in the "NepRWA_Potential_Dams" coverage. Culverts and other non-fam fish passage obstacles are summarized in a culvert coverage. Note that much of the attribute data for this coverage is stored in a seperate database and must be attached to the coverage using a join or relate. Also note that scans of original field data sheets along with photos are stored in pdf filed for each site.
